# calculate distortion for a range of number of cluster
distortions = []
for i in range(1, 11):
    km = KMeans(
        n_clusters=i, init='random',
        n_init=10, max_iter=300,
        tol=1e-04, random_state=0
    )
    km.fit(df[['md','grain_density']])
    distortions.append(km.inertia_)

# plot
plt.plot(range(1, 11), distortions, marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')
plt.ylabel('Distortion')
plt.show()

In [164]:
from sklearn import linear_model
#from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score

# Create linear regression object
regr = linear_model.LinearRegression()
cluster_selected=0

for cluster in df['cluster'].unique():
    for predictor in ['phi_best','kh_kl_log',]:
        # Train the model using the training sets
        regr.fit(df[keepColumns][df['cluster']==cluster], df[predictor][df['cluster']==cluster])

        # Make predictions using the testing set
        predictions = regr.predict(df[keepColumns][df['cluster']==cluster])

        # 
        #plt.scatter(df[predictor][df['cluster']==cluster], predictions)

        #plt.xlabel('Measured'), plt.ylabel('Predicted'), plt.title('Porosity for cluster {:d}'.format(cluster))
        #plt.xlim([0,50]),plt.ylim([0,50])
        #plt.show()
        
        filename='regr__'+ predictor+'__cluster'+ str(cluster) + '.pkl'
        pickle.dump(regr, open(filename, 'wb'))

from sklearn import decomposition
pca = decomposition.PCA(n_components=3)

pca.fit(df.drop(columns=['kh_kl', 'kv_kl','phi_best']))
X = pca.transform(df.drop(columns=['kh_kl', 'kv_kl','phi_best']))
